@kalafut would you mind giving this another spin to see if it's fixed for you?  I was able to reproduce on my iPhone 15 in Safari and was able to find a fix. I don't have an iPhone 14 to test on; and want to make sure it's fixed with your browser / setup.

Please re-open if the issue is still observed.

Thank you for the report ðŸ™‡

> If the user prefers reduced motion (via the `prefers-reduce-motion` media query) we should instead show a freeze frame of the ghost animation (i.e. not let it animate at all).

This already seems to be the case for me? I also see this in the AnimatedTerminal component: 
```ts 
    if (reducedMotion) {
      setCurrentFrame(20);
      return;
    }
```
Is it possible this issue is already solved?
